title: Vertex AI - Delete a dataset or annotation set
abstract:
# Vertex AI - Delete a dataset or annotation set
An contains the labels associated with the uploaded source files within a Dataset. An Annotation set is associated with a data type and an objective.
When you no longer need a particular annotation set, you can use the Google Cloud console to delete it.
- In the Vertex AI section, go to  the **Datasets** page. [Go to the Datasets page](https://console.cloud.google.com/vertex-ai/datasets) 
- Select your project.
- Select the checkbox corresponding to the dataset or annotation set you  want to remove.
- Clickmore_vert **View more** .  List of options appears.
- Select **Delete dataset**
